						<div class="postbody">Blargg's NTSC filter covers the vast majority of &quot;unexpected&quot; changes from clean pixels to a real NES environment. The NTSC conversion creates several types of artifacts (most notably with 50% dither), but everything beyond this is really just things like colour gamut and scanlines, kinda superficial stuff.<br /><br />If you're running windows, you can get a ready-made build of blargg's program here: <!-- l --><a class="postlink-local" href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=21&amp;t=11947">viewtopic.php?f=21&amp;t=11947</a><!-- l --><br /><br />Here's what your last image looks like through the NTSC filter:<br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<a href="./download/file.php?id=5551&amp;mode=view"><img src="./download/file.php?id=5551&amp;t=1" alt="test3_filtered.png" /></a><br />
			<span class="gensmall">test3_filtered.png [ 169.69 KiB | Viewed 2221 times ]</span>
		

		<br />
	</div></div>

