					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">No need to test on hardware given blargg's NTSC filter -- what you see above is pretty much what you'll see on actual hardware (hues/etc. are going to vary based on people's TV screens though).<br /><br />As for the teal reflection: welcome to the NES's limited palette (and when drawing graphics in editors like YY-CHR, no palette there is ever going to match the NES perfectly, sorry to say) and NTSC (a.k.a. &quot;Never The Same Colour&quot;).  This is one of several reasons why an artist seeing their work on real hardware (or as close as possible -- blargg's stuff is pretty damn accurate) is important.</div>

