					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">WheelInventor wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">the ntsc thingy made the mountain reflection very teal. Maybe a bit weird?</div><br />The NTSC demo program lets you control contrast and sharpness with the mouse, I think I took the picture with high contrast. In general, though, this is to be expected when you go between different TVs and monitors, relative contrast of colours is going to vary a lot.<br /><br />Brightness is consistent up and down a single hue column, but when you're mixing colours on the same row especially, different TVs will shift the brightness of various hues up and down. It won't be a robust relationship.</div>

